WEBVTT

1
00:00:24.042 --> 00:00:27.042
[thunder rumbles softly]

2
00:01:11.292 --> 00:01:14.292
[car engine revving]

3
00:01:19.709 --> 00:01:22.584
[song on car radio]
♪ All day long I'm racin' ♪

4
00:01:22.667 --> 00:01:24.709
♪ Get up to the floor ♪

5
00:01:24.792 --> 00:01:27.792
[chilling music]

6
00:01:34.084 --> 00:01:36.001
- [car engine revving]
- ♪ Get me out ♪

7
00:01:36.084 --> 00:01:39.501
♪ Think I've lost control ♪

8
00:01:39.584 --> 00:01:41.292
♪ Get me out ♪

9
00:01:43.167 --> 00:01:45.084
[car engine revving]

10
00:01:45.167 --> 00:01:48.167
[loud music on car radio]

11
00:01:49.334 --> 00:01:52.501
♪ Get it out get it out
Get it out come on ♪

12
00:01:52.584 --> 00:01:54.251
[♪♪♪]

13
00:01:54.334 --> 00:01:59.251
♪ I gotta run back run back
Around the sun ♪

14
00:01:59.334 --> 00:02:01.251
[car engine revving]

15
00:02:01.334 --> 00:02:05.709
♪ Get it out get it out
Before I lose my mind ♪

16
00:02:05.792 --> 00:02:07.251
[loud thump]

17
00:02:08.417 --> 00:02:10.917
[truck horn blaring]

18
00:02:13.709 --> 00:02:15.542
[car tires screeching]

19
00:02:16.876 --> 00:02:18.626
♪ ...I'm runnin' ♪

20
00:02:18.709 --> 00:02:21.709
- [James panting]
- ♪ Runnin' from my past ♪

21
00:02:23.667 --> 00:02:25.584
[Mary] Oh. come on.

22
00:02:25.667 --> 00:02:27.626
- [running footsteps]
- [Mary panting]

23
00:02:27.709 --> 00:02:29.751
You've got to be kidding me.

24
00:02:29.834 --> 00:02:31.209
- ♪ Get me out ♪

25
00:02:31.292 --> 00:02:32.459
[car door opens]

26
00:02:32.542 --> 00:02:34.167
[music stops]

27
00:02:34.251 --> 00:02:36.334
- I am so sorry. I--

28
00:02:36.417 --> 00:02:38.001
Are you okay?

29
00:02:38.084 --> 00:02:39.667
- Yeah.
No. I'm fine. I'm fine.

30
00:02:39.751 --> 00:02:41.667
- Here. let me help you.

31
00:02:41.751 --> 00:02:44.751
- [both panting]

32
00:02:45.751 --> 00:02:46.751
- Uh...

33
00:02:49.751 --> 00:02:50.917
Sorry about all this.

34
00:02:51.001 --> 00:02:52.209
[bus honking]

35
00:02:52.292 --> 00:02:53.751
- [Mary] Sure. okay.
- [James] I got it.

36
00:02:53.834 --> 00:02:55.001
- The latch is broken.

37
00:02:56.292 --> 00:02:57.542
[grunts]
Shoot. that's my bus.

38
00:02:57.626 --> 00:02:59.209
Hey.

39
00:02:59.292 --> 00:03:01.792
Hey. Hey. hey! Wait!

40
00:03:04.376 --> 00:03:08.084
- Hang on. I got it.
[groans] Oh. fuck.

41
00:03:08.167 --> 00:03:10.167
[bus honking]

42
00:03:10.251 --> 00:03:12.542
- You can just...
Sorry.

43
00:03:12.626 --> 00:03:14.334
[bus door closes]

44
00:03:14.417 --> 00:03:15.709
- [groans]

45
00:03:15.792 --> 00:03:18.792
[bus departing]

46
00:03:21.126 --> 00:03:23.459
[James] Well. I'm officially
an asshole.

47
00:03:23.542 --> 00:03:24.834
Where were you heading?

48
00:03:24.917 --> 00:03:26.376
[Mary] The city.

49
00:03:26.459 --> 00:03:28.334
Where were you going?

50
00:03:28.417 --> 00:03:29.792
- Just up the pass.

51
00:03:31.459 --> 00:03:34.126
- I guess
it wasn't meant to be.

52
00:03:34.209 --> 00:03:36.834
- So what are you gonna do?

53
00:03:36.917 --> 00:03:38.667
- Can just head back
into town. I guess.

54
00:03:45.917 --> 00:03:47.501
[James] What's it called?

55
00:03:47.584 --> 00:03:49.876
[Mary] Silent Hill.

56
00:03:49.959 --> 00:03:51.501
There's a trail down that way.

57
00:03:52.917 --> 00:03:53.876
- Cool.

58
00:03:53.959 --> 00:03:55.792
What's that down there
on the water?

59
00:03:58.667 --> 00:04:01.167
- That's the Lakeview.

60
00:04:01.251 --> 00:04:03.042
It's a hotel.

61
00:04:03.126 --> 00:04:06.334
The view of the lake
from the rooftop is so pretty.

62
00:04:06.417 --> 00:04:09.376
- Pretty enough
they named a hotel after it?

63
00:04:09.459 --> 00:04:10.417
- You nearly run me down.

64
00:04:10.501 --> 00:04:13.209
and now you're giving me
a hard time?

65
00:04:13.292 --> 00:04:14.792
- Yeah. shit. Sorry. Um...

66
00:04:16.126 --> 00:04:17.042
- [chuckles]

67
00:04:17.126 --> 00:04:18.584
- I deserved that. didn't I?

68
00:04:18.667 --> 00:04:21.709
Mm. I'm James. by the way.

69
00:04:21.792 --> 00:04:22.834
- Mary.

70
00:04:22.917 --> 00:04:25.209
- Well. like. seriously. Mary.
let me drive you home.

71
00:04:25.292 --> 00:04:27.626
I can save you
a sprained ankle or two.

72
00:04:27.709 --> 00:04:30.292
- I don't even know you. James.

73
00:04:30.376 --> 00:04:32.792
- All right. Well. I'm just
gonna have to stand here.

74
00:04:32.876 --> 00:04:35.167
watch you go down.
make sure you don't fall.

75
00:04:35.251 --> 00:04:36.417
- Seems like
appropriate penance

76
00:04:36.501 --> 00:04:38.376
for screwing up my day.

77
00:04:38.459 --> 00:04:39.584
[birds chirping]

78
00:04:39.667 --> 00:04:40.876
- [sniffles]

79
00:04:47.334 --> 00:04:49.376
- So. are you coming or what?

80
00:04:58.209 --> 00:05:00.917
[suitcases thudding]

81
00:05:03.501 --> 00:05:04.584
[hood shuts]

82
00:05:07.292 --> 00:05:09.917
[wind whooshing]

83
00:05:10.001 --> 00:05:13.001
[ominous burst of music]

84
00:05:28.001 --> 00:05:29.876
- Silent Hill summer storm.

85
00:05:31.084 --> 00:05:33.376
Doesn't happen often.

86
00:05:33.459 --> 00:05:35.042
But when it does...

87
00:05:40.209 --> 00:05:42.042
- [gasps sharply]

88
00:05:42.126 --> 00:05:45.126
[club music playing]

89
00:05:46.126 --> 00:05:49.126
[phone vibrating]

90
00:05:50.167 --> 00:05:51.292
[sniffles]

91
00:06:01.167 --> 00:06:02.792
[beer mug clanks]

92
00:06:03.959 --> 00:06:05.584
- Think it's time to go.

93
00:06:06.959 --> 00:06:10.001
- All right. All right.

94
00:06:10.084 --> 00:06:11.126
[James groans]

95
00:06:11.209 --> 00:06:12.251
- Jesus!
- [glass shatters]

96
00:06:12.334 --> 00:06:13.626
[James] Sorry.

97
00:06:13.709 --> 00:06:14.751
Sorry. That's on me.

98
00:06:14.834 --> 00:06:17.001
[Bouncer] Let's go. asshole.

99
00:06:17.084 --> 00:06:18.667
[grunts and groans]

100
00:06:18.751 --> 00:06:19.917
[furniture clattering]

101
00:06:20.001 --> 00:06:23.001
[phone vibrating]

102
00:06:26.959 --> 00:06:28.959
- [Man] Get outta here.
- [Bouncer] Let's go. Let's go.

103
00:06:29.959 --> 00:06:31.042
[James] Yeah? Come on!

104
00:06:33.001 --> 00:06:34.376
Come on!

105
00:06:34.459 --> 00:06:36.501
Yo. get the fuck off me!

106
00:06:36.584 --> 00:06:38.792
Let go of me! [grunts]

107
00:06:40.292 --> 00:06:42.792
Fuck you! Fuck you!

108
00:06:42.876 --> 00:06:44.001
[men grunt with effort]

109
00:06:45.626 --> 00:06:47.292
[Bouncer] Nighty night. fucker.

110
00:06:47.376 --> 00:06:49.751
[rock music playing]

111
00:06:49.834 --> 00:06:51.667
[door slams]

112
00:06:52.876 --> 00:06:55.917
[phone vibrating]

113
00:07:01.167 --> 00:07:02.709
[James groans]

114
00:07:02.792 --> 00:07:04.501
[M] [over phone]
There you are.

115
00:07:04.584 --> 00:07:06.126
How are you?

116
00:07:07.167 --> 00:07:09.292
[James] [over phone]
Not so great.

117
00:07:09.376 --> 00:07:10.751
[M] You've been drinking.

118
00:07:12.917 --> 00:07:15.709
It felt like we were moving
in the right direction. James.

119
00:07:15.792 --> 00:07:17.709
- I know. [groans]

120
00:07:17.792 --> 00:07:19.834
[M] [over phone] You've got
to stop beating yourself up.

121
00:07:19.917 --> 00:07:21.209
[James sighs]

122
00:07:21.292 --> 00:07:22.959
- Here's what I need you to do.

123
00:07:23.042 --> 00:07:25.876
Get home. drink some water.
get some sleep.

124
00:07:25.959 --> 00:07:28.584
Reset and come
to our appointment tomorrow.

125
00:07:29.584 --> 00:07:34.001
- Yeah. tomorrow.
Yeah. Okay.

126
00:07:35.417 --> 00:07:36.792
We'll see.

127
00:07:38.126 --> 00:07:40.292
[claps of thunder]

128
00:07:40.376 --> 00:07:43.417
[heavy downpour of rain]

129
00:07:48.584 --> 00:07:49.792
[lock clicks. door opens]

130
00:07:53.251 --> 00:07:54.542
[door slams shut]

131
00:07:57.376 --> 00:07:58.376
[keys thud]

132
00:07:59.917 --> 00:08:01.834
[James sighs deeply]

133
00:08:01.917 --> 00:08:05.917
[rain pattering]

134
00:08:08.376 --> 00:08:11.376
[disturbing music playing]

135
00:08:19.167 --> 00:08:22.167
[sharp gasp.
groaning in pain]

136
00:08:28.167 --> 00:08:29.917
Oh. God.

137
00:08:30.001 --> 00:08:31.834
[bottle thuds. rolling]

138
00:08:38.167 --> 00:08:41.167
[unsettling music playing]

139
00:08:57.167 --> 00:09:00.167
[mellow music playing]

140
00:09:04.584 --> 00:09:07.584
[thunder rumbles]

141
00:09:09.126 --> 00:09:12.167
[Mary] James.
so much time has passed.

142
00:09:12.251 --> 00:09:13.709
- [keys jingling]
- I know that.

143
00:09:13.792 --> 00:09:15.292
But I'm asking--

144
00:09:15.376 --> 00:09:18.001
I'm begging you
to please come back.

145
00:09:19.417 --> 00:09:21.001
To our place.

146
00:09:22.459 --> 00:09:24.042
Something's happened.

147
00:09:25.209 --> 00:09:28.292
Please. James. I need you.

148
00:09:30.084 --> 00:09:33.251
Love. Mary.

149
00:09:48.584 --> 00:09:51.584
[rain pattering]

150
00:09:53.167 --> 00:09:56.167
[car engine revs]

151
00:10:06.042 --> 00:10:07.042
[car engine stops]

152
00:10:14.167 --> 00:10:15.542
[loud clap of thunder]

153
00:10:15.626 --> 00:10:17.709
- Jesus.
- [car door shuts]

154
00:10:17.792 --> 00:10:20.792
[rain pattering on car roof]

155
00:10:29.959 --> 00:10:31.001
[James] [voice-over]
It's her.

156
00:10:35.459 --> 00:10:37.542
It's always been her.

157
00:10:40.542 --> 00:10:41.834
Mary.

158
00:10:45.709 --> 00:10:47.376
The girl of my dreams.

159
00:10:48.876 --> 00:10:50.626
The love of my life.

160
00:10:57.709 --> 00:11:00.709
[coughing]

161
00:11:05.751 --> 00:11:07.751
[breathing heavily]

162
00:11:11.751 --> 00:11:12.751
[car door opens]

163
00:11:19.501 --> 00:11:20.501
[car door closes]

164
00:11:21.501 --> 00:11:24.501
[crunching footsteps]

165
00:11:29.459 --> 00:11:31.542
[door creaks open]

166
00:11:42.501 --> 00:11:45.501
[faucets clatter]

167
00:11:53.084 --> 00:11:56.084
[pensive music playing]

168
00:12:11.001 --> 00:12:12.584
[James] [voice-over]
Our place.

169
00:12:19.917 --> 00:12:21.167
Our town.

170
00:12:23.501 --> 00:12:24.501
[car beeps]

171
00:12:27.042 --> 00:12:28.417
Our love.

172
00:12:33.334 --> 00:12:34.626
It was here.

173
00:12:40.334 --> 00:12:42.251
It was everywhere.

174
00:12:44.501 --> 00:12:47.501
[uneasy music playing]

175
00:12:50.709 --> 00:12:53.292
And now. they keep telling me
to let go.

176
00:12:57.042 --> 00:12:58.334
To move on.

177
00:13:04.834 --> 00:13:07.209
But how can I ever do that?

178
00:13:12.084 --> 00:13:14.501
When you're calling me?

179
00:13:45.501 --> 00:13:48.501
[rustling]

180
00:13:55.542 --> 00:13:56.709
Hello?

181
00:13:59.751 --> 00:14:01.126
- Grab a bag.

182
00:14:01.209 --> 00:14:02.251
- What?

183
00:14:08.459 --> 00:14:10.459
[Angela] Careful.

184
00:14:10.542 --> 00:14:11.751
They're heavy.

185
00:14:14.001 --> 00:14:16.459
- So. where's all this
coming from?

186
00:14:16.542 --> 00:14:18.417
[Angela] This?

187
00:14:18.501 --> 00:14:20.542
You mean the ashes?

188
00:14:20.626 --> 00:14:21.751
[James] Yeah.

189
00:14:22.751 --> 00:14:26.001
[Angela] It started with
the fires in the summer.

190
00:14:26.084 --> 00:14:27.751
[panting]
Tore through the forests.

191
00:14:29.626 --> 00:14:32.251
Some are still burning.

192
00:14:32.334 --> 00:14:35.001
And then came the rains.

193
00:14:35.084 --> 00:14:37.126
- Right.

194
00:14:37.209 --> 00:14:39.751
So. there's someone...

195
00:14:39.834 --> 00:14:42.251
someone I care about.
and I need to find her.

196
00:14:43.959 --> 00:14:45.167
- [panting] You won't.

197
00:14:46.751 --> 00:14:49.667
Floods overran
the water treatment plant.

198
00:14:49.751 --> 00:14:51.001
When water
gets contaminated.

199
00:14:51.084 --> 00:14:53.584
people don't stick around.

200
00:14:53.667 --> 00:14:55.584
- Look. I'm still going to try
and head into town

201
00:14:55.667 --> 00:14:57.001
if you could just...

202
00:15:01.501 --> 00:15:03.001
Well...

203
00:15:03.084 --> 00:15:04.751
thanks. anyway.

204
00:15:04.834 --> 00:15:05.834
- Wait.

205
00:15:07.167 --> 00:15:10.042
You don't find
who you're looking for.

206
00:15:10.126 --> 00:15:13.292
you can always
come back and find me.

207
00:15:13.376 --> 00:15:14.501
I'm Angela.

208
00:15:15.501 --> 00:15:16.792
- Angela.

209
00:15:16.876 --> 00:15:18.042
Sure.

210
00:15:37.376 --> 00:15:40.417
[soft dramatic music playing]

211
00:15:41.917 --> 00:15:43.042
[Mary sighs]

212
00:15:43.126 --> 00:15:46.417
[James] So. what if I...

213
00:15:46.501 --> 00:15:47.709
moved here?

214
00:15:49.417 --> 00:15:52.209
- No museums. No clubs.

215
00:15:52.292 --> 00:15:53.834
Zero anonymity.

216
00:15:53.917 --> 00:15:57.084
- Yeah. I'm just
as shocked as you are.

217
00:15:57.167 --> 00:15:58.709
- You'd really
want to move here?

218
00:15:58.792 --> 00:16:00.292
- I would.

219
00:16:00.376 --> 00:16:01.459
- Why?

220
00:16:01.542 --> 00:16:04.501
- Well. there's this girl.

221
00:16:04.584 --> 00:16:08.292
And she's not much
to look at. but.

222
00:16:08.376 --> 00:16:09.459
[kissing]

223
00:16:11.751 --> 00:16:12.917
What?

224
00:16:13.001 --> 00:16:15.292
You don't think we're ready
to live together?

225
00:16:15.376 --> 00:16:17.626
- There are parts of me
you haven't seen.

226
00:16:18.959 --> 00:16:20.667
What if who I am scares you?

227
00:16:21.876 --> 00:16:23.084
- It won't.

228
00:16:24.251 --> 00:16:25.876
I promise you.

229
00:16:30.459 --> 00:16:32.042
[kissing]

230
00:16:36.251 --> 00:16:37.626
Hey. Hey. hey. hey.

231
00:16:37.709 --> 00:16:39.126
Hey now. now tilt
your head back.

232
00:16:39.209 --> 00:16:40.626
[Mary groans]

233
00:16:40.709 --> 00:16:42.417
[both laughing]

234
00:16:42.501 --> 00:16:43.459
[Mary]
I can't believe this.

235
00:16:43.542 --> 00:16:45.626
[James] It's okay. I got you.

236
00:16:45.709 --> 00:16:49.334
I'm here.
I'll always be here.

237
00:16:49.417 --> 00:16:51.584
I mean it.

238
00:16:58.501 --> 00:17:01.501
[disturbing rhythmic drumbeats]

239
00:17:19.917 --> 00:17:22.917
[ominous music playing]

240
00:17:56.584 --> 00:17:58.209
[glass squeaks]

241
00:18:06.084 --> 00:18:07.084
I don't understand.

242
00:18:08.917 --> 00:18:11.917
[flies buzzing]

243
00:18:20.084 --> 00:18:23.084
[panting]

244
00:18:25.292 --> 00:18:26.459
[whispers] This is insane.

245
00:18:29.042 --> 00:18:32.042
[running footsteps]

246
00:18:33.917 --> 00:18:36.917
[breathing heavily]

247
00:18:48.584 --> 00:18:49.751
[shouts] Hello?!

248
00:18:51.959 --> 00:18:54.001
Can anyone hear me?

249
00:18:54.084 --> 00:18:56.417
[music heard in the distance]

250
00:19:00.584 --> 00:19:02.001
Is someone there?

251
00:19:02.084 --> 00:19:04.126
[music on speaker]

252
00:19:04.209 --> 00:19:06.251
Hello?

253
00:19:06.334 --> 00:19:09.334
[solemn music
playing on speaker]

254
00:19:27.501 --> 00:19:30.501
[faint music playing]

255
00:19:31.501 --> 00:19:34.501
[running footsteps]

256
00:19:36.501 --> 00:19:39.501
[music gets louder]

257
00:19:49.501 --> 00:19:52.501
[man snoring]

258
00:20:01.001 --> 00:20:02.084
Hello?

259
00:20:05.084 --> 00:20:06.542
Can you hear me?

260
00:20:11.167 --> 00:20:12.709
[metal clanks]

261
00:20:14.709 --> 00:20:17.709
[static on radio]

262
00:20:26.001 --> 00:20:28.501
- [James gasps]
- They're coming back.

263
00:20:28.584 --> 00:20:30.959
- Who?
- You know they're coming back.

264
00:20:31.042 --> 00:20:33.667
All that darkness.
you can't keep it away.

265
00:20:33.751 --> 00:20:35.876
- Just-just-just
get off me. all right?

266
00:20:35.959 --> 00:20:37.167
[panting in fear]

267
00:20:40.709 --> 00:20:43.709
[phone vibrating]

268
00:20:46.542 --> 00:20:49.167
- I wasn't expecting
a no-show. James.

269
00:20:49.251 --> 00:20:50.667
- I'm in Silent Hill.

270
00:20:50.751 --> 00:20:51.834
[M] [over phone] What?

271
00:20:51.917 --> 00:20:53.584
- I did--something's
happened here.

272
00:20:53.667 --> 00:20:55.626
Something really. really bad.

273
00:20:55.709 --> 00:20:56.667
[M] James.

274
00:20:56.751 --> 00:20:58.292
Listen to me carefully.

275
00:20:58.376 --> 00:21:00.251
This is getting out of control.

276
00:21:00.334 --> 00:21:01.751
[James] I need to go home...

277
00:21:01.834 --> 00:21:03.334
to Mary.

278
00:21:03.417 --> 00:21:04.959
[M] What did you say?

279
00:21:05.042 --> 00:21:06.542
I need you to come back.

280
00:21:06.626 --> 00:21:08.417
There's no home
for you there anymore.

281
00:21:08.501 --> 00:21:10.001
[signage buzzing]

282
00:21:10.084 --> 00:21:11.459
[M] James?

283
00:21:13.501 --> 00:21:14.417
James?

284
00:21:14.501 --> 00:21:15.667
- [groaning]

285
00:21:17.292 --> 00:21:20.292
[crunching footsteps]

286
00:21:21.292 --> 00:21:24.292
[signage buzzing]

287
00:21:33.292 --> 00:21:36.292
- [groaning]

288
00:21:38.667 --> 00:21:41.709
[static noise from radio]

289
00:21:44.501 --> 00:21:45.917
[creature screeches]

290
00:22:01.251 --> 00:22:04.417
[club music playing on speaker]

291
00:22:07.126 --> 00:22:08.376
[Mary] Everyone...

292
00:22:08.459 --> 00:22:09.376
this is James.

293
00:22:09.459 --> 00:22:10.376
- Hi.

294
00:22:10.459 --> 00:22:12.334
[Claudette] So Mary tells me
you're an artist.

295
00:22:12.417 --> 00:22:13.917
[James] Yeah. Painter.

296
00:22:14.001 --> 00:22:16.459
[Claudette] And you have
the perfect muse.

297
00:22:18.209 --> 00:22:20.876
- Our Mary.
she's something special.

298
00:22:20.959 --> 00:22:24.001
- Sparkling little apple
of her father's eye.

299
00:22:24.084 --> 00:22:25.876
- Oh. so you all know him. or...?

300
00:22:25.959 --> 00:22:27.042
- [chuckling]

301
00:22:27.126 --> 00:22:28.292
- Know him?

302
00:22:28.376 --> 00:22:30.417
Joshua Crane.

303
00:22:30.501 --> 00:22:33.167
Doesn't quite do it justice
when you say it out loud.

304
00:22:33.251 --> 00:22:34.751
- [in unison]
He changed our lives.

305
00:22:34.834 --> 00:22:36.209
- Mary's family.

306
00:22:36.292 --> 00:22:37.626
they built this town.

307
00:22:37.709 --> 00:22:39.251
Gave us purpose.

308
00:22:39.334 --> 00:22:43.376
- My life was spinning out
in all directions.

309
00:22:43.459 --> 00:22:46.209
Helped me put my head
back on straight.

310
00:22:46.292 --> 00:22:48.584
- I think we all
have a similar story.

311
00:22:48.667 --> 00:22:49.626
Mm.

312
00:22:49.709 --> 00:22:53.751
- We have a way of seeing things
here in Silent Hill.

313
00:22:53.834 --> 00:22:55.584
But don't worry.

314
00:22:55.667 --> 00:22:57.876
- I'm sure
we'll find a place for you.

315
00:23:02.251 --> 00:23:03.667
- [screams outside]

316
00:23:06.542 --> 00:23:07.792
[footsteps]

317
00:23:09.542 --> 00:23:10.626
- What is that?

318
00:23:11.834 --> 00:23:13.334
[flesh melting]

319
00:23:22.292 --> 00:23:25.292
[radio crackling]

320
00:23:28.959 --> 00:23:30.417
Who is that?!

321
00:23:33.209 --> 00:23:36.209
[sinister music playing]

322
00:23:38.334 --> 00:23:39.667
[creature shrieks]

323
00:23:43.542 --> 00:23:44.626
- [straining effort]

324
00:23:44.709 --> 00:23:47.167
[creature screeches]

325
00:23:53.084 --> 00:23:56.001
[trembling breath]

326
00:23:56.084 --> 00:23:59.001
[tense music playing]

327
00:23:59.084 --> 00:24:00.709
[metallic clatter]

328
00:24:06.084 --> 00:24:08.084
[breathing heavily]

329
00:24:10.042 --> 00:24:10.959
[static from radio]

330
00:24:11.042 --> 00:24:14.084
[Man] This is the Silent Hill
Emergency Operations System.

331
00:24:14.167 --> 00:24:16.542
This is not a test.

332
00:24:16.626 --> 00:24:18.917
City officials have issued
a health emergency

333
00:24:19.001 --> 00:24:21.501
for the city of Silent Hill
and surrounding areas.

334
00:24:21.584 --> 00:24:22.792
Residents are being ordered

335
00:24:22.876 --> 00:24:25.292
to evacuate this
area immediately.

336
00:24:27.459 --> 00:24:30.251
I repeat. this is not a test.

337
00:24:30.334 --> 00:24:32.292
What you are hearing
is not a test.

338
00:24:32.376 --> 00:24:34.459
This is the emergency
alert system.

339
00:24:34.542 --> 00:24:37.959
Civil authorities are issuing--
- [emergency alert blaring]

340
00:24:38.042 --> 00:24:41.042
[wings flapping]

341
00:24:50.917 --> 00:24:53.917
[ground cracking]

342
00:25:22.167 --> 00:25:24.167
[creature screeches]

343
00:25:44.709 --> 00:25:46.709
[footsteps clanging]

344
00:25:48.667 --> 00:25:50.001
[James groans in pain]

345
00:25:53.417 --> 00:25:54.751
[rats squeaking]

346
00:25:58.084 --> 00:26:01.084
[James grunts with effort]

347
00:26:02.709 --> 00:26:05.709
[rats squeaking]

348
00:26:13.292 --> 00:26:14.292
[pipe clanging]

349
00:26:16.834 --> 00:26:18.834
[squelching]

350
00:26:22.501 --> 00:26:24.626
[insects chittering]

351
00:26:30.584 --> 00:26:33.626
[footsteps clanging]

352
00:26:44.084 --> 00:26:47.084
[eerie shrieking]

353
00:26:51.292 --> 00:26:54.292
[tense music playing]

354
00:27:09.292 --> 00:27:11.292
[James grunts]

355
00:27:21.792 --> 00:27:24.792
[straining]

356
00:27:34.709 --> 00:27:37.709
[insects chittering]

357
00:27:43.084 --> 00:27:44.417
[James grunts]

358
00:27:45.876 --> 00:27:47.876
[insects chittering]

359
00:27:51.084 --> 00:27:52.084
[yells in pain]

360
00:27:56.542 --> 00:27:58.001
[panting]

361
00:27:58.084 --> 00:28:01.084
[insects bustling]

362
00:28:09.292 --> 00:28:12.292
[soft tense music playing]

363
00:28:30.542 --> 00:28:31.959
[eerie squeal]

364
00:28:34.042 --> 00:28:35.667
[Mary] [whispers] James.

365
00:28:38.959 --> 00:28:40.292
- Mary?

366
00:28:42.626 --> 00:28:44.459
[soft. suspenseful
music playing]

367
00:28:49.084 --> 00:28:51.251
- Hello. handsome.

368
00:28:51.334 --> 00:28:53.667
How many times you get lost
this time around?

369
00:28:53.751 --> 00:28:55.459
- I just can't believe
how much stuff I had.

370
00:28:55.542 --> 00:28:56.709
- Come on. one last push.

371
00:28:56.792 --> 00:28:57.792
- Um-hmm.

372
00:28:58.792 --> 00:28:59.792
[kissing]

373
00:29:01.584 --> 00:29:02.792
- Let me help you with this.

374
00:29:02.876 --> 00:29:04.084
- Ooh. why thank you.

375
00:29:04.167 --> 00:29:05.834
[Mary] [chuckles softly]
You're so welcome.

376
00:29:08.917 --> 00:29:11.834
[tense music]

377
00:29:11.917 --> 00:29:14.917
[footsteps approaching]

378
00:29:40.292 --> 00:29:41.876
[door hinges squeak]

379
00:29:51.501 --> 00:29:54.501
[white noise from TV]

380
00:30:18.292 --> 00:30:21.292
[grunting in pain]

381
00:30:36.667 --> 00:30:37.667
[phone ringing]

382
00:30:38.667 --> 00:30:40.959
[James panting over phone]

383
00:30:41.042 --> 00:30:42.042
- Where are you?

384
00:30:43.959 --> 00:30:45.584
- [groaning] It hurts so bad.
I can't...

385
00:30:45.667 --> 00:30:47.584
I can't make it stop.

386
00:30:47.667 --> 00:30:50.209
- It's gonna be okay.
Just tell me where you are.

387
00:30:50.292 --> 00:30:51.959
[James] No. No.

388
00:30:52.042 --> 00:30:53.501
No. I can feel her.

389
00:30:53.584 --> 00:30:55.084
She's close.

390
00:30:56.084 --> 00:30:57.501
I think she's--

391
00:30:57.584 --> 00:31:00.584
- James? James?

392
00:31:01.584 --> 00:31:04.084
- [panting]

393
00:31:04.167 --> 00:31:05.417
[groaning]

394
00:31:10.834 --> 00:31:14.709
[heavy downpour]

395
00:31:23.042 --> 00:31:25.334
[thunder roaring]

396
00:31:26.584 --> 00:31:29.917
[rain pattering]

397
00:31:35.834 --> 00:31:36.834
[voicemail]
The mailbox is full

398
00:31:36.917 --> 00:31:38.917
and cannot accept
any messages at this time.

399
00:31:39.001 --> 00:31:41.001
Goodbye.

400
00:31:41.084 --> 00:31:42.084
[phone thuds]

401
00:31:45.667 --> 00:31:46.751
[phone clicking]

402
00:31:51.584 --> 00:31:53.001
[Man] Hello?

403
00:31:53.084 --> 00:31:54.626
- It's me.

404
00:31:54.709 --> 00:31:56.959
Yes. One of my patients
who's broken protocol.

405
00:31:57.042 --> 00:31:58.626
I need a wellness check.

406
00:31:58.709 --> 00:32:00.334
[Man] Which patient?

407
00:32:00.417 --> 00:32:01.959
- James Sunderland.

408
00:32:02.042 --> 00:32:03.251
[Man] Is he a danger
to himself or anyone?

409
00:32:03.334 --> 00:32:05.626
- I wouldn't say dangerous but...

410
00:32:05.709 --> 00:32:07.417
he's in trouble.

411
00:32:07.501 --> 00:32:10.626
[rain pattering]

412
00:32:10.709 --> 00:32:12.751
[metal clanks]

413
00:32:16.959 --> 00:32:18.167
[rain pattering]

414
00:32:21.126 --> 00:32:22.292
[door opens]

415
00:32:22.376 --> 00:32:23.667
[James panting]

416
00:32:32.834 --> 00:32:34.584
[wings flapping]

417
00:32:34.667 --> 00:32:36.084
[James groans]

418
00:32:39.167 --> 00:32:41.501
[James panting]

419
00:32:41.584 --> 00:32:43.126
[tense music]

420
00:33:07.334 --> 00:33:09.084
[door opens]

421
00:33:11.167 --> 00:33:13.376
- [keys thud]
- Mare?

422
00:33:16.334 --> 00:33:19.334
[distant chanting]

423
00:33:24.209 --> 00:33:26.792
- We understand completely
how you feel. [echoes]

424
00:33:30.501 --> 00:33:32.459
- Love is not an easy thing.
[echoes]

425
00:33:37.126 --> 00:33:39.126
- You can get your head
all twisted around.

426
00:33:39.209 --> 00:33:41.084
- You can lose
yourself in it. [echoes]

427
00:33:46.292 --> 00:33:48.292
- But we need to stay focused.

428
00:33:49.292 --> 00:33:50.376
[door creaks]

429
00:33:52.042 --> 00:33:55.834
- And here he is.
The man of the house.

430
00:33:57.709 --> 00:34:00.042
- What's going on. Jimmy boy?

431
00:34:01.126 --> 00:34:02.417
- What's going on here?

432
00:34:02.501 --> 00:34:04.209
[footsteps]

433
00:34:04.292 --> 00:34:05.792
[soft tense music]

434
00:34:17.626 --> 00:34:21.209
Okay. What the fuck was that?

435
00:34:21.292 --> 00:34:22.959
- I'm sorry.
They just showed up.

436
00:34:23.042 --> 00:34:23.959
- Wait. they just showed up?

437
00:34:24.042 --> 00:34:25.751
Twenty people
just showed up?

438
00:34:25.834 --> 00:34:28.084
Again?
They're fucking weird. Mary.

439
00:34:28.167 --> 00:34:31.251
- They're my family. James.

440
00:34:31.334 --> 00:34:33.876
They took me in
after my father died.

441
00:34:37.459 --> 00:34:38.501
- All right.

442
00:34:42.709 --> 00:34:45.709
[uneasy music playing]

443
00:34:48.292 --> 00:34:49.876
Is that him?

444
00:34:52.376 --> 00:34:53.751
- [blowing]

445
00:34:58.126 --> 00:34:59.042
[closet door closes]

446
00:34:59.126 --> 00:35:00.167
[sighs]

447
00:35:03.417 --> 00:35:05.876
Please. James...

448
00:35:05.959 --> 00:35:07.751
Please.

449
00:35:07.834 --> 00:35:09.834
I want this to be
about you and me.

450
00:35:12.126 --> 00:35:13.209
Always.

451
00:35:14.459 --> 00:35:16.417
Always just us.

452
00:35:18.667 --> 00:35:21.667
[tense music]

453
00:35:22.917 --> 00:35:25.917
[wings flapping]

454
00:35:29.626 --> 00:35:30.792
[James sighs]

455
00:35:45.126 --> 00:35:47.834
- Brookhaven Hospital?

456
00:35:47.917 --> 00:35:49.334
[distant coughing]

457
00:35:50.709 --> 00:35:53.709
[gagging]

458
00:35:55.042 --> 00:35:56.251
[coughing]

459
00:36:02.251 --> 00:36:03.459
- What the fuck?

460
00:36:03.542 --> 00:36:04.459
- Are you okay?

461
00:36:04.542 --> 00:36:06.667
- It look like I'm okay?

462
00:36:06.751 --> 00:36:07.667
[breathing heavily]

463
00:36:07.751 --> 00:36:08.917
Who the hell are you?

464
00:36:09.001 --> 00:36:11.584
- I'm-I'm James. I'm--

465
00:36:11.667 --> 00:36:14.667
- Wait. why are you not sick
like everyone else?

466
00:36:14.751 --> 00:36:18.417
- What? No. I'm-I'm looking
for someone.

467
00:36:18.501 --> 00:36:19.417
[Eddie] Ain't nobody here.

468
00:36:19.501 --> 00:36:20.626
[James]
No. they're at the hospital.

469
00:36:20.709 --> 00:36:22.584
- [scoffs]

470
00:36:22.667 --> 00:36:25.001
[laughing]

471
00:36:25.084 --> 00:36:26.042
- What's funny?

472
00:36:26.126 --> 00:36:27.959
- Look around. buddy.

473
00:36:28.042 --> 00:36:29.917
Won't find anyone
at the hospital.

474
00:36:30.001 --> 00:36:32.126
City's one big cemetery.

475
00:36:34.334 --> 00:36:35.376
- Oh. God.
What is happening?

476
00:36:35.459 --> 00:36:37.417
- You should have seen it.

477
00:36:37.501 --> 00:36:40.292
No one could get their ass
in gear to react in time.

478
00:36:40.376 --> 00:36:41.584
Poor fucks.

479
00:36:41.667 --> 00:36:44.626
Whole town was rotten
before anyways. but this.

480
00:36:44.709 --> 00:36:46.542
this was something else.

481
00:36:46.626 --> 00:36:48.334
The fires...

482
00:36:48.417 --> 00:36:50.251
the water...

483
00:36:50.334 --> 00:36:52.334
everybody going insane.

484
00:36:52.417 --> 00:36:54.667
bleeding to death
out on the streets.

485
00:36:54.751 --> 00:36:56.542
All that crazy shit happened.

486
00:36:56.626 --> 00:36:58.292
and then these things
start to show up.

487
00:36:58.376 --> 00:37:00.542
[breathing hard]

488
00:37:02.292 --> 00:37:03.792
Wow.

489
00:37:03.876 --> 00:37:05.542
You've been lucky so far.

490
00:37:05.626 --> 00:37:06.626
- What?

491
00:37:08.126 --> 00:37:09.792
- Check this.

492
00:37:09.876 --> 00:37:10.959
- Jesus Christ.

493
00:37:11.042 --> 00:37:13.626
- [panting]

494
00:37:13.709 --> 00:37:17.042
So. what is it you do?

495
00:37:17.126 --> 00:37:18.042
- What do you mean.
what do I do?

496
00:37:18.126 --> 00:37:19.042
- In life. What do you do?

497
00:37:19.126 --> 00:37:20.126
- I'm a--I'm a painter.

498
00:37:20.209 --> 00:37:21.709
- A painter. huh?

499
00:37:21.792 --> 00:37:24.209
I ever heard of you?

500
00:37:24.292 --> 00:37:25.334
- I really don't know.

501
00:37:27.626 --> 00:37:30.501
- Always thought I had
the goods to be an artist.

502
00:37:30.584 --> 00:37:31.626
You ever have weird dreams?

503
00:37:34.917 --> 00:37:39.626
The shit that goes on in there.
you couldn't handle it.

504
00:37:39.709 --> 00:37:42.209
[baby screaming]

505
00:37:43.251 --> 00:37:44.334
[James] Do you hear that?

506
00:37:44.417 --> 00:37:45.792
- Hear what?

507
00:37:45.876 --> 00:37:47.334
- Sounds like a baby.

508
00:37:47.417 --> 00:37:48.709
- A baby?

509
00:37:48.792 --> 00:37:49.917
There ain't no baby here.

510
00:37:51.292 --> 00:37:53.584
[footsteps]

511
00:37:53.667 --> 00:37:55.792
- Can I ask a question?

512
00:37:56.959 --> 00:37:58.751
Why would you stay here?

513
00:37:58.834 --> 00:38:00.001
- You kidding?

514
00:38:00.084 --> 00:38:02.626
Place is rid of
all these assholes.

515
00:38:02.709 --> 00:38:04.042
It's heaven now.

516
00:38:04.126 --> 00:38:06.959
Got the entire city to myself.

517
00:38:07.042 --> 00:38:08.126
[distant baby cooing]

518
00:38:08.209 --> 00:38:09.501
- There...

519
00:38:12.459 --> 00:38:14.042
What the hell is this?

520
00:38:17.626 --> 00:38:18.792
Holy shit.

521
00:38:18.876 --> 00:38:20.667
- Uh-uh. be careful.

522
00:38:20.751 --> 00:38:22.459
- What are you talking about?
It's just a kid.

523
00:38:23.501 --> 00:38:27.042
Hey. what's your name?
I'm James.

524
00:38:27.126 --> 00:38:28.042
And this is--

525
00:38:28.126 --> 00:38:29.126
- Eddie.

526
00:38:31.001 --> 00:38:32.126
- I'm Laura.

527
00:38:32.209 --> 00:38:34.001
[James] Laura?

528
00:38:34.084 --> 00:38:36.167
Oh. you can't just stay in there
all by yourself. Laura.

529
00:38:36.251 --> 00:38:37.376
Come on. I think
you might be small enough

530
00:38:37.459 --> 00:38:38.667
to get through these bars.

531
00:38:38.751 --> 00:38:39.667
Come on.

532
00:38:39.751 --> 00:38:40.667
[Eddie] Let's get out of here.

533
00:38:40.751 --> 00:38:43.126
[James] Come on. it's okay.
You can trust me.

534
00:38:43.209 --> 00:38:44.709
You can trust me. Come on.

535
00:38:44.792 --> 00:38:46.542
- I'm telling you.
this is a bad idea.

536
00:38:46.626 --> 00:38:47.792
[James] Come on. Laura.

537
00:38:47.876 --> 00:38:49.459
I got you. Come on.
We can help you.

538
00:38:52.292 --> 00:38:53.667
[loud crackle.
radio screeches]

539
00:38:55.542 --> 00:38:56.876
- We need to get
our asses outta here.

540
00:38:56.959 --> 00:38:57.959
- Come on. Laura.
It's all right.

541
00:38:58.042 --> 00:38:59.751
We're not gonna leave
without you. Come on.

542
00:38:59.834 --> 00:39:00.751
Just a bit closer.

543
00:39:00.834 --> 00:39:01.751
Come on. Laura.
- [distant growling]

544
00:39:01.834 --> 00:39:02.751
- Come on.
- [Laura gasps]

545
00:39:02.834 --> 00:39:04.667
[Eddie] Jimmy. let's go!

546
00:39:04.751 --> 00:39:06.126
[James groans]

547
00:39:07.126 --> 00:39:08.292
[metal scraping]

548
00:39:10.751 --> 00:39:12.251
- Would you look at that?

549
00:39:12.334 --> 00:39:15.292
You're all fucked up
like everyone else.

550
00:39:15.376 --> 00:39:16.751
[heavy footsteps]

