[elevator rising]

827
01:00:45.126 --> 01:00:46.334
- [breathing heavily]

828
01:00:46.417 --> 01:00:47.834
[whispers] Help.

829
01:00:49.959 --> 01:00:50.959
- Here. Let me see.

830
01:00:52.376 --> 01:00:53.334
[blood splatters]

831
01:00:53.417 --> 01:00:54.542
Oh. no.

832
01:00:55.792 --> 01:00:57.417
- [groans in pain]

833
01:01:03.042 --> 01:01:05.001
- [straining]

834
01:01:05.084 --> 01:01:06.709
[grunting]

835
01:01:10.376 --> 01:01:12.167
[Maria groaning]

836
01:01:19.417 --> 01:01:21.417
- [breathing heavily]

837
01:01:25.001 --> 01:01:26.084
[James groans]

838
01:01:36.626 --> 01:01:37.959
[doors squeak]

839
01:01:41.209 --> 01:01:44.209
[panting]

840
01:01:46.834 --> 01:01:49.626
- [gasps. groaning]

841
01:01:55.251 --> 01:01:57.209
You can say it.

842
01:01:57.292 --> 01:01:58.751
- What?

843
01:01:59.834 --> 01:02:01.584
- I look just like her.

844
01:02:04.209 --> 01:02:07.251
- No. No. no. no.
How would you know that?

845
01:02:07.334 --> 01:02:09.917
- It's how you look at me.

846
01:02:10.001 --> 01:02:12.292
- [breathing deeply]

847
01:02:12.376 --> 01:02:16.709
Look. I'm gonna go upstairs.
I want you to stay here.

848
01:02:16.792 --> 01:02:18.084
- [grunts]
No. don't leave me.

849
01:02:18.167 --> 01:02:19.209
- You'll be safer here.

850
01:02:19.292 --> 01:02:21.501
I'm gonna look for Mary.
and I'll come right back.

851
01:02:21.584 --> 01:02:23.834
- Promise me something.

852
01:02:23.917 --> 01:02:26.626
If you find out she's gone.
we leave.

853
01:02:26.709 --> 01:02:28.001
Together.

854
01:02:28.084 --> 01:02:29.542
We don't look back.

855
01:02:37.084 --> 01:02:38.584
- [strains with effort]

856
01:02:44.001 --> 01:02:45.251
[Laura] Who is she?

857
01:02:50.042 --> 01:02:51.667
- Just someone
I'm trying to help.

858
01:02:54.251 --> 01:03:00.334
Now. Laura. you have to
tell me where Mary is.

859
01:03:00.417 --> 01:03:02.084
- Doesn't look like
you want to find her.

860
01:03:02.167 --> 01:03:05.876
- No. I do.
It's all I want.

861
01:03:05.959 --> 01:03:09.251
Now. please. where is she?

862
01:03:09.334 --> 01:03:10.626
- My baby's sad!

863
01:03:10.709 --> 01:03:13.709
[doll bawling]

864
01:03:19.584 --> 01:03:22.584
He's cold and sad.

865
01:03:22.667 --> 01:03:25.292
Sad because nobody loved him.

866
01:03:25.376 --> 01:03:27.376
Just like Mary.

867
01:03:27.459 --> 01:03:29.292
- What?

868
01:03:29.376 --> 01:03:33.042
- You left her all
[shrieks] alone!

869
01:03:35.126 --> 01:03:36.334
- Ah!

870
01:03:37.292 --> 01:03:39.751
- You have to get to her
before it's too late.

871
01:03:44.251 --> 01:03:46.167
- No. wait! Laura!

872
01:03:47.667 --> 01:03:48.667
Laura!

873
01:03:52.292 --> 01:03:55.292
[footsteps thudding on stairs]

874
01:04:08.042 --> 01:04:10.251
Why are you doing this?

875
01:04:10.334 --> 01:04:11.876
- No one said
it would be easy.

876
01:04:13.167 --> 01:04:16.042
[door opens. squeaks]

877
01:04:20.626 --> 01:04:23.001
- [panting]

878
01:04:23.084 --> 01:04:24.417
No.

879
01:04:27.459 --> 01:04:29.042
[door opens. squeaks]

880
01:04:30.459 --> 01:04:32.501
What?

881
01:04:32.584 --> 01:04:33.959
Laura?

882
01:04:36.376 --> 01:04:37.501
- [giggles]

883
01:04:37.584 --> 01:04:39.501
- Laura?!
- [door closes]

884
01:04:40.376 --> 01:04:41.584
- Laura?!

885
01:04:41.667 --> 01:04:43.251
Laura. open the door!

886
01:04:45.209 --> 01:04:47.876
- [banging on door]
- Open the door!

887
01:04:47.959 --> 01:04:51.042
[strange growls]

888
01:05:14.792 --> 01:05:15.709
[loud shrieks]

889
01:05:15.792 --> 01:05:17.417
[hospital bed sliding]

890
01:05:25.501 --> 01:05:28.501
[bed clanking]

891
01:05:31.501 --> 01:05:33.001
[Laura]
Why'd you come. James?

892
01:05:38.251 --> 01:05:40.209
What did you think you'd find?

893
01:05:57.459 --> 01:05:58.834
[blood drips]

894
01:06:00.251 --> 01:06:01.334
[James] Mary.

895
01:06:17.709 --> 01:06:18.626
[pipe clanks to floor]

896
01:06:18.709 --> 01:06:21.709
[James choking]

897
01:06:22.876 --> 01:06:26.209
[Laura] Come back
when you're ready. James.

898
01:06:26.292 --> 01:06:28.376
- [choking]
- [Doctor] Mr. Sunderland?

899
01:06:28.459 --> 01:06:30.459
Mr. Sunderland?

900
01:06:30.542 --> 01:06:32.626
Are you with us. Mr. Sunderland?

901
01:06:32.709 --> 01:06:34.417
[heart monitor beeping]

902
01:06:34.501 --> 01:06:36.001
- What?

903
01:06:36.084 --> 01:06:37.126
What's going on?

904
01:06:37.209 --> 01:06:39.001
What's going on?
Where am I?

905
01:06:39.084 --> 01:06:40.334
Where am I?

906
01:06:40.417 --> 01:06:41.584
- Brookhaven Hospital.

907
01:06:41.667 --> 01:06:43.084
Silent Hill.

908
01:06:44.334 --> 01:06:45.251
- Where is she?

909
01:06:46.292 --> 01:06:47.626
Where is she?

910
01:06:47.709 --> 01:06:48.626
- Where is who?

911
01:06:48.709 --> 01:06:50.167
- Mary. Mary Crane.

912
01:06:50.251 --> 01:06:51.876
[footsteps approaching]

913
01:06:53.584 --> 01:06:54.584
What?

914
01:06:58.542 --> 01:06:59.876
- Hello. James.

915
01:07:00.792 --> 01:07:04.501
- I know where she is.
[breathes heavily]

916
01:07:06.626 --> 01:07:08.584
- You need to let go of her.

917
01:07:09.501 --> 01:07:10.959
She's gone.

918
01:07:12.917 --> 01:07:14.959
She's dead. James.

919
01:07:17.626 --> 01:07:20.209
She's been dead
for months now.

920
01:07:20.292 --> 01:07:22.084
You know that.

921
01:07:26.667 --> 01:07:29.376
- Why would you say that?

922
01:07:29.459 --> 01:07:32.417
[eerie ambient music]

923
01:07:32.501 --> 01:07:34.209
[M] We've got a lot
of serious work to do.

924
01:07:35.459 --> 01:07:36.834
But we'll get you through it.

925
01:07:38.334 --> 01:07:40.584
You just have to
promise me something.

926
01:07:44.084 --> 01:07:45.751
You need to want to
see yourself get better

927
01:07:45.834 --> 01:07:47.584
as much as I do.

928
01:08:01.084 --> 01:08:04.084
[emotional music playing]

929
01:08:09.709 --> 01:08:12.709
[car approaching]

930
01:08:33.584 --> 01:08:34.792
[door opens]

931
01:08:42.084 --> 01:08:44.042
[Mary] Why are you
sitting in the dark?

932
01:08:45.709 --> 01:08:47.167
[suitcase slides]

933
01:08:47.251 --> 01:08:49.042
- Pack your things.

934
01:08:49.126 --> 01:08:51.626
I want us out of here.

935
01:08:51.709 --> 01:08:53.709
- Why are you acting like this?

936
01:08:55.251 --> 01:08:57.042
- Guess what I did today.

937
01:08:58.709 --> 01:09:01.209
I saw this girl
across the street...

938
01:09:03.292 --> 01:09:04.792
so I followed her.

939
01:09:04.876 --> 01:09:06.292
[Mary] Stop.

940
01:09:06.376 --> 01:09:08.542
- I went down this long
flight of stairs.

941
01:09:08.626 --> 01:09:10.084
[Mary] Stop.

942
01:09:10.167 --> 01:09:12.834
- And I saw these monsters.

943
01:09:12.917 --> 01:09:14.751
I saw them tear her apart.

944
01:09:14.834 --> 01:09:17.251
- Just stop!
- [glass shatters]

945
01:09:21.792 --> 01:09:23.751
- How long?

946
01:09:23.834 --> 01:09:25.417
- Since I was a girl.

947
01:09:27.751 --> 01:09:30.792
- Why would your father
do this to you?

948
01:09:30.876 --> 01:09:32.001
- I don't know.

949
01:09:33.667 --> 01:09:35.126
I never had a choice.

950
01:09:37.667 --> 01:09:39.501
- This is your last chance.

951
01:09:41.001 --> 01:09:43.501
Walk out that door with me now.

952
01:09:43.584 --> 01:09:44.584
- Not when you're like this.

953
01:09:44.667 --> 01:09:45.917
- What am I like?

954
01:09:46.792 --> 01:09:47.792
- Scared.

955
01:09:48.834 --> 01:09:50.834
- You think I'm scared?

956
01:09:50.917 --> 01:09:52.917
[raises voice]
I am not scared!

957
01:09:53.001 --> 01:09:55.584
I am not scared of any of you.

958
01:09:55.667 --> 01:09:58.001
[Mary whimpers]

959
01:09:58.084 --> 01:10:00.501
- But you're disgusted.

960
01:10:00.584 --> 01:10:01.709
Say it.

961
01:10:02.626 --> 01:10:04.959
Say I'm disgusting to you.
Say it!

962
01:10:07.251 --> 01:10:11.251
That day. I was leaving.

963
01:10:11.334 --> 01:10:13.751
I was leaving.
and then you showed up.

964
01:10:16.792 --> 01:10:19.334
- Why-why didn't you
just tell me?

965
01:10:19.417 --> 01:10:21.584
- Because I knew you'd walk away.

966
01:10:23.834 --> 01:10:26.334
I see the way
you're looking at me.

967
01:10:26.417 --> 01:10:29.126
That'll never change now.

968
01:10:29.209 --> 01:10:33.709
I told you there were things.
You-you promised me.

969
01:10:33.792 --> 01:10:36.792
[emotional music]

970
01:10:41.792 --> 01:10:44.001
[footsteps receding]

971
01:10:54.834 --> 01:10:56.167
[car alarm beeps]

972
01:10:59.251 --> 01:11:00.667
[car door opens]

973
01:11:22.709 --> 01:11:23.709
[car door shuts]

974
01:11:29.459 --> 01:11:31.376
[Doctor] How is he today?

975
01:11:31.459 --> 01:11:33.042
[M] Calm. I guess.

976
01:11:34.376 --> 01:11:38.584
I've worked with vets.
all kinds of trauma.

977
01:11:38.667 --> 01:11:42.501
but this is different.
He won't let me in at all.

978
01:11:42.584 --> 01:11:44.376
- How long have you
been treating him?

979
01:11:44.459 --> 01:11:46.292
- Almost a year.

980
01:11:47.542 --> 01:11:49.417
But it's gotten worse.

981
01:11:49.501 --> 01:11:53.501
That woman. Mary.
she was everything to him.

982
01:11:54.584 --> 01:11:55.626
Since he lost her.

983
01:11:55.709 --> 01:11:58.167
it's like he lost
his grip on reality.

984
01:11:58.251 --> 01:12:00.834
and his desire to regain it.

985
01:12:03.209 --> 01:12:05.542
Mary died after their breakup.

986
01:12:06.876 --> 01:12:08.917
And he just won't accept it.

987
01:12:09.001 --> 01:12:11.917
[birds chirping]

988
01:12:12.001 --> 01:12:15.001
[emotional music playing]

989
01:12:18.251 --> 01:12:20.417
It's good to see you up. James.

990
01:12:21.834 --> 01:12:23.917
How are you feeling today?

991
01:12:26.751 --> 01:12:28.209
James?

992
01:12:32.792 --> 01:12:34.667
- I just wish...

993
01:12:36.126 --> 01:12:38.459
I wish I hadn't let her down.

994
01:12:42.126 --> 01:12:44.334
- You're blaming yourself. but...

995
01:12:46.126 --> 01:12:49.251
all this chaos in your mind...

996
01:12:49.334 --> 01:12:50.917
it's not real.

997
01:12:52.667 --> 01:12:58.501
It's not real.
and it almost destroyed you.

998
01:12:58.584 --> 01:13:00.751
We can still fix this.

999
01:13:00.834 --> 01:13:03.292
But it's got to be
your decision.

1000
01:13:08.001 --> 01:13:11.626
- Thank you.
For everything.

1001
01:13:16.376 --> 01:13:19.376
[footsteps receding]

1002
01:13:31.292 --> 01:13:34.292
[tense. sinister music playing]

1003
01:13:39.376 --> 01:13:42.709
[wings flapping]

1004
01:13:42.792 --> 01:13:45.792
[emergency alarm blaring]

1005
01:13:54.417 --> 01:13:57.417
[walls crackling]

1006
01:14:07.042 --> 01:14:08.959
[Maria] You didn't find her?

1007
01:14:13.876 --> 01:14:17.626
Then we can leave.
Together.

1008
01:14:19.667 --> 01:14:21.709
[groans]

1009
01:14:21.792 --> 01:14:24.542
You promised. James.

1010
01:14:27.501 --> 01:14:30.501
[emotional music playing]

1011
01:14:31.709 --> 01:14:34.042
- You look just like her.

1012
01:14:36.167 --> 01:14:38.459
- I never told you my name.

1013
01:14:42.292 --> 01:14:43.626
It's Maria.

1014
01:14:47.709 --> 01:14:50.667
[kissing]

1015
01:14:57.751 --> 01:15:00.376
Or we can stay here together...

1016
01:15:00.459 --> 01:15:02.667
if you want.

1017
01:15:02.751 --> 01:15:04.334
Just us.

1018
01:15:11.376 --> 01:15:12.542
What is it?

1019
01:15:14.751 --> 01:15:17.626
Where are you going?

1020
01:15:17.709 --> 01:15:19.334
[breathing heavily]

1021
01:15:22.667 --> 01:15:23.917
James.

1022
01:15:24.001 --> 01:15:25.334
Wait for me.

1023
01:15:27.334 --> 01:15:28.959
You won't find her down there.

1024
01:15:31.126 --> 01:15:32.709
[elevator clanks]

1025
01:15:33.792 --> 01:15:35.334
[elevator pings]

1026
01:15:37.751 --> 01:15:39.001
Please.

1027
01:15:44.917 --> 01:15:47.917
[elevator door closing]

1028
01:15:51.876 --> 01:15:53.459
[elevator pings]

1029
01:15:54.459 --> 01:15:56.876
[elevator in free fall]

1030
01:15:56.959 --> 01:15:58.751
Why are you doing this?

1031
01:15:58.834 --> 01:16:00.834
[tense music playing]

1032
01:16:04.417 --> 01:16:06.251
You were free of all this pain.

1033
01:16:11.292 --> 01:16:12.334
James!

1034
01:16:19.001 --> 01:16:20.292
James!

1035
01:16:21.417 --> 01:16:22.417
James!

1036
01:16:24.334 --> 01:16:25.584
James!

1037
01:16:25.667 --> 01:16:27.417
[elevator powering down]

1038
01:16:32.542 --> 01:16:34.042
[elevator door opening]

1039
01:16:36.626 --> 01:16:38.251
You can't go in there.

1040
01:16:56.667 --> 01:16:58.001
Let's go back.

1041
01:17:00.209 --> 01:17:01.834
We can still go back.

1042
01:17:06.126 --> 01:17:08.292
Please don't go any further.

1043
01:17:26.667 --> 01:17:28.917
It's over
if you want it to be.

1044
01:17:34.834 --> 01:17:36.667
- Mary's not dead.

1045
01:17:38.167 --> 01:17:39.459
Not to me.

1046
01:17:41.251 --> 01:17:42.792
And you're not real.

1047
01:17:44.584 --> 01:17:46.626
You're just in my way.

1048
01:17:46.709 --> 01:17:47.917
- No.

1049
01:17:48.001 --> 01:17:50.167
No. no.
No. no. no. no. no.

1050
01:17:50.251 --> 01:17:51.626
Look at me. James.

1051
01:17:54.459 --> 01:17:56.376
- Goodbye. Maria.

1052
01:17:56.459 --> 01:17:58.209
[lights flickering. clanking]

1053
01:18:00.542 --> 01:18:02.626
- [screams in pain]

1054
01:18:04.709 --> 01:18:06.751
[wet squelching]

1055
01:18:10.917 --> 01:18:12.709
[blood spurting]

1056
01:18:37.876 --> 01:18:40.917
[rhythmic heavy clanking]

1057
01:19:00.501 --> 01:19:01.501
[bottle clanks]

1058
01:19:12.292 --> 01:19:13.626
[James groans]

1059
01:19:15.584 --> 01:19:18.584
[water splashes.
blooping softly]

1060
01:19:38.292 --> 01:19:41.292
- [gasping for air]

1061
01:19:44.876 --> 01:19:46.709
[breathing heavily]

1062
01:19:51.501 --> 01:19:54.501
[flames roaring]

1063
01:20:10.709 --> 01:20:13.709
[roaring fire]

1064
01:20:16.959 --> 01:20:19.959
[flames roaring]

1065
01:20:22.167 --> 01:20:23.542
[distant thud]

1066
01:20:32.876 --> 01:20:34.334
[Laura] You're finally here.

1067
01:20:36.376 --> 01:20:37.417
- Laura?

1068
01:20:37.501 --> 01:20:38.501
[Laura giggles]

1069
01:20:41.126 --> 01:20:44.209
[soft music playing]

1070
01:20:44.292 --> 01:20:46.376
[giggles]

1071
01:20:48.876 --> 01:20:50.917
[James] I'm not playing
anymore. Laura.

1072
01:20:52.959 --> 01:20:54.751
- Do you think
you're ready to face it?

1073
01:20:59.751 --> 01:21:02.584
Do you think
you're ready to face us?

1074
01:21:02.667 --> 01:21:03.709
- [shuddering]

1075
01:21:07.751 --> 01:21:09.751
[doll cooing]

1076
01:21:15.084 --> 01:21:17.334
[James] Why are you
doing this to me?

1077
01:21:17.417 --> 01:21:19.167
- To help you remember.

1078
01:21:21.126 --> 01:21:22.792
What's her name?

1079
01:21:22.876 --> 01:21:24.167
- What?

1080
01:21:24.251 --> 01:21:25.209
- Think. James.

1081
01:21:25.292 --> 01:21:26.417
- [groans]

1082
01:21:28.709 --> 01:21:30.334
- What's Mary's full name?

1083
01:21:32.959 --> 01:21:34.542
- [groans]

1084
01:21:34.626 --> 01:21:36.459
- Our full name. James...

1085
01:21:37.751 --> 01:21:39.251
- [groans]

1086
01:21:44.709 --> 01:21:47.292
[breathing heavily]

1087
01:21:47.376 --> 01:21:48.834
[Laura] It's time now.

1088
01:21:50.876 --> 01:21:52.709
[flames crackling]

1089
01:21:55.376 --> 01:21:58.667
And now.
there's nothing left to hide.

1090
01:22:01.001 --> 01:22:02.459
[flames crackling]

1091
01:22:10.751 --> 01:22:11.876
[door closes]

1092
01:22:11.959 --> 01:22:14.126
[eerie ambient music]

1093
01:22:14.209 --> 01:22:16.292
[Angela sobbing]

1094
01:22:25.084 --> 01:22:27.251
- Haven't you had enough?

1095
01:22:27.334 --> 01:22:28.584
Disgusting.

1096
01:22:28.667 --> 01:22:29.792
You're disgusting!

1097
01:22:33.126 --> 01:22:35.334
You--you see.

1098
01:22:35.417 --> 01:22:37.251
Please tell me
you can see it.

1099
01:22:40.667 --> 01:22:43.001
I can't get away from him.

1100
01:22:43.084 --> 01:22:45.959
He'll never stop hurting me.

1101
01:22:47.417 --> 01:22:49.126
- Let me help you.

1102
01:22:49.209 --> 01:22:50.667
- Don't! Don't.

1103
01:22:50.751 --> 01:22:52.042
Stay away.

1104
01:22:52.126 --> 01:22:54.084
[sobbing]

1105
01:22:55.501 --> 01:22:56.709
- Please.

1106
01:23:00.626 --> 01:23:01.792
[grunts]

1107
01:23:20.709 --> 01:23:22.751
[growling softly]

1108
01:23:32.292 --> 01:23:34.417
[James breathing heavily]

1109
01:23:40.459 --> 01:23:42.251
[tense music]

1110
01:23:44.209 --> 01:23:45.834
[growling softy]

1111
01:23:47.834 --> 01:23:49.126
[James] Mary?

1112
01:23:49.209 --> 01:23:50.542
[growling]

1113
01:24:11.751 --> 01:24:12.959
[whispers] I'm sorry.

1114
01:24:14.334 --> 01:24:15.376
[squeals]

1115
01:24:30.459 --> 01:24:33.459
- [door opens]
- [fire roaring]

1116
01:24:40.834 --> 01:24:42.251
Mary?!

1117
01:24:46.167 --> 01:24:47.584
No. wait!

1118
01:24:47.667 --> 01:24:49.084
[running footsteps]

1119
01:24:52.042 --> 01:24:53.167
[door opens]

1120
01:25:01.376 --> 01:25:04.376
[fire crackling]

1121
01:25:33.542 --> 01:25:36.542
[music playing on radio]

1122
01:25:43.459 --> 01:25:45.292
[M] You need to let go of her.

1123
01:25:47.626 --> 01:25:49.042
She's gone.

1124
01:25:50.917 --> 01:25:52.834
She's dead. James.

1125
01:25:55.542 --> 01:25:58.084
She's been dead for months now.

1126
01:25:58.167 --> 01:25:59.834
You know that.

1127
01:26:06.709 --> 01:26:08.876
[birds chirping]

1128
01:26:25.459 --> 01:26:27.042
[Mary] You came.

1129
01:26:27.126 --> 01:26:28.334
- Of course.

1130
01:26:30.292 --> 01:26:31.459
As soon as I could.

1131
01:26:31.542 --> 01:26:33.001
[Mary] It's okay.

1132
01:26:33.751 --> 01:26:35.667
- I never should have left.

1133
01:26:35.751 --> 01:26:38.334
[Mary] Whether you would've
stayed or not.

1134
01:26:38.417 --> 01:26:41.126
I still would've gotten sick.

1135
01:26:41.209 --> 01:26:43.251
[James] Well. maybe
I could've helped.

1136
01:26:43.334 --> 01:26:44.917
- No one could've.

1137
01:26:46.251 --> 01:26:48.501
My father poisoned me.

1138
01:26:49.917 --> 01:26:52.167
He poisoned me my whole life.

1139
01:26:56.001 --> 01:26:58.251
I tried to shield you from it.

1140
01:26:59.459 --> 01:27:01.042
- I know.

1141
01:27:03.042 --> 01:27:05.251
[Mary] Can you help me lie down?

1142
01:27:10.501 --> 01:27:12.001
[James] Sure.

1143
01:27:12.084 --> 01:27:15.084
[emotional music
playing on radio]

1144
01:27:28.626 --> 01:27:31.792
- Okay.
Okay. okay. okay.

1145
01:27:33.751 --> 01:27:35.084
- [groans]

1146
01:27:44.542 --> 01:27:45.542
- [silent sobs]

1147
01:27:51.834 --> 01:27:53.042
[glass breaks]

1148
01:27:55.126 --> 01:27:56.876
Come on.

1149
01:27:56.959 --> 01:27:58.834
There you go.

1150
01:27:58.917 --> 01:28:00.501
All right.

1151
01:28:06.376 --> 01:28:08.292
Just tell me
how I can help you.

1152
01:28:09.917 --> 01:28:11.626
- You know.

1153
01:28:11.709 --> 01:28:13.042
- [sniffles]

1154
01:28:14.459 --> 01:28:17.251
- He's lived inside of me
for so long.

1155
01:28:18.542 --> 01:28:20.459
I don't want him there anymore.

1156
01:28:21.126 --> 01:28:22.167
- I can't do that.

1157
01:28:22.251 --> 01:28:23.709
- I want to be free.

1158
01:28:26.792 --> 01:28:28.501
Please. James.

1159
01:28:29.751 --> 01:28:31.167
Please.

1160
01:28:35.001 --> 01:28:36.876
Help me now.

1161
01:28:36.959 --> 01:28:38.459
- [James sobbing]

1162
01:28:40.459 --> 01:28:42.459
[emotional music
playing on radio]

1163
01:28:53.792 --> 01:28:55.501
[crying]

1164
01:29:29.917 --> 01:29:31.667
[wings flapping]

1165
01:29:44.501 --> 01:29:46.751
[ground crumbling]

1166
01:30:02.334 --> 01:30:05.376
[ethereal music playing]

1167
01:30:29.959 --> 01:30:31.542
[ground crumbling]

1168
01:30:36.042 --> 01:30:39.626
[emotional music playing]

1169
01:30:52.876 --> 01:30:55.876
[wings flapping]

1170
01:31:01.792 --> 01:31:06.334
That day. I should've
died with you.

1171
01:31:12.251 --> 01:31:14.334
[wings flapping]

1172
01:31:14.417 --> 01:31:17.042
You forgave me...

1173
01:31:21.376 --> 01:31:23.834
but I could never
forgive myself.

1174
01:31:36.917 --> 01:31:38.792
I'm ready now.

1175
01:31:42.792 --> 01:31:44.876
No matter what it takes.

1176
01:31:49.251 --> 01:31:51.792
No matter where it takes us.

1177
01:32:00.001 --> 01:32:02.042
This time...

1178
01:32:05.626 --> 01:32:07.584
I won't let go.

1179
01:32:17.917 --> 01:32:19.792
[car engine revving]

1180
01:32:23.292 --> 01:32:25.251
[water splashes]

1181
01:33:21.626 --> 01:33:23.126
[Doctor]
Mr. Sunderland?

1182
01:33:24.459 --> 01:33:25.751
Mr. Sunderland?

1183
01:33:25.834 --> 01:33:27.251
[truck honking]

1184
01:33:28.417 --> 01:33:30.376
[Doctor]
Are you with us. Mr. Sunderland?

1185
01:33:31.376 --> 01:33:32.376
[truck honking]

1186
01:33:32.459 --> 01:33:38.001
[tire screeching]

1187
01:33:40.626 --> 01:33:42.334
[breathing heavily] What?

1188
01:33:45.167 --> 01:33:46.209
[Mary] Oh. come on.

1189
01:33:46.292 --> 01:33:49.084
[running footsteps]

1190
01:33:49.167 --> 01:33:50.459
You've got to be kidding me.

1191
01:33:50.542 --> 01:33:53.542
[emotional music]

1192
01:33:58.084 --> 01:33:59.709
- I'm so sorry.

1193
01:34:01.584 --> 01:34:02.709
Are you okay?

1194
01:34:02.792 --> 01:34:04.167
- Yeah.
No. I'm fine. I'm fine.

1195
01:34:10.709 --> 01:34:12.167
Are you okay?

1196
01:34:13.251 --> 01:34:14.542
- I think so.

1197
01:34:24.876 --> 01:34:26.042
It's okay. I got it.

1198
01:34:29.126 --> 01:34:30.459
The latch is broken.

1199
01:34:30.542 --> 01:34:31.459
- How do you know that?

1200
01:34:31.542 --> 01:34:34.084
[distant honking]

1201
01:34:35.667 --> 01:34:37.084
Shoot. that's my bus.

1202
01:34:38.417 --> 01:34:40.001
Hey. wait!

1203
01:34:44.209 --> 01:34:45.834
[suitcase latch snaps]

1204
01:34:45.917 --> 01:34:47.751
[horn honks]

1205
01:34:47.834 --> 01:34:49.917
Sorry. just...

1206
01:34:50.001 --> 01:34:51.709
[bus engine revs]

1207
01:34:53.959 --> 01:34:55.959
- Where were you heading?

1208
01:34:56.042 --> 01:34:57.501
- The next city.

1209
01:34:57.584 --> 01:35:01.126
- Well. I just ruined your day.

1210
01:35:01.209 --> 01:35:04.292
Wouldn't be much of a gentleman
if I didn't try and help fix it.

1211
01:35:04.376 --> 01:35:05.876
- A gentleman?

1212
01:35:05.959 --> 01:35:07.917
Didn't know
they made those anymore.

1213
01:35:08.001 --> 01:35:10.001
- Gentleman named James.

1214
01:35:10.084 --> 01:35:12.459
- I'm--
- Mary.

1215
01:35:12.542 --> 01:35:14.126
I saw it on your case.

1216
01:35:15.751 --> 01:35:17.167
- [chuckles]

1217
01:35:19.709 --> 01:35:21.126
[car hood shuts]

1218
01:35:24.584 --> 01:35:26.709
[wind blows]

1219
01:35:28.417 --> 01:35:29.792
You're a painter?

1220
01:35:31.292 --> 01:35:32.501
- Yeah.

1221
01:35:35.709 --> 01:35:36.792
[car door closes]

1222
01:35:43.751 --> 01:35:45.292
- What do you paint?

1223
01:35:51.709 --> 01:35:54.959
[car engine starts. revving]

1224
01:35:55.042 --> 01:35:58.042
[funky music playing]

1225
01:36:00.959 --> 01:36:02.501
[car tires screech]

1226
01:36:39.501 --> 01:36:42.501
[static noise]

1227
01:36:48.751 --> 01:36:51.792
["Letter - from the Lost Days"
by Akira Yamaoka]

1228
01:37:17.542 --> 01:37:21.417
♪ A letter to my future self ♪

1229
01:37:21.501 --> 01:37:24.876
♪ Am I still happy? I began ♪

1230
01:37:24.959 --> 01:37:28.501
♪ Have I grown more pretty ♪

1231
01:37:28.584 --> 01:37:32.417
♪ Is Daddy still a good man? ♪

1232
01:37:32.501 --> 01:37:35.709
♪ Am I still friends
With Colleen ♪

1233
01:37:35.792 --> 01:37:39.959
♪ I'm sure that
I'm still laughing ♪

1234
01:37:40.042 --> 01:37:42.792
♪ Aren't I? ♪

1235
01:37:42.876 --> 01:37:45.501
♪ Aren't I? ♪

1236
01:37:54.042 --> 01:37:57.626
♪ Hey there to my future self ♪

1237
01:37:57.709 --> 01:38:01.417
♪ If you forget how to smile ♪

1238
01:38:01.501 --> 01:38:04.709
♪ I have this to tell you ♪

1239
01:38:04.792 --> 01:38:08.459
♪ Remember it once in a while ♪

1240
01:38:08.542 --> 01:38:12.376
♪ Ten years ago
Your past self ♪

1241
01:38:12.459 --> 01:38:15.792
♪ Prayed for your happiness ♪

1242
01:38:15.876 --> 01:38:23.001
♪ Please don't lose hope ♪

1243
01:38:23.084 --> 01:38:29.917
♪ Oh oh what a pair
Me and you ♪

1244
01:38:30.001 --> 01:38:37.417
♪ Put here to feel joy
Not be blue ♪

1245
01:38:37.501 --> 01:38:44.917
♪ Sad times and bad times
See them through ♪

1246
01:38:45.001 --> 01:38:51.709
♪ Soon we will know
If it's for real ♪

1247
01:38:51.792 --> 01:38:59.417
♪ What we both feel ♪

1248
01:38:59.501 --> 01:39:01.334
♪ Though I can't know for sure ♪

1249
01:39:01.417 --> 01:39:03.292
♪ How things worked out for us ♪

1250
01:39:05.042 --> 01:39:06.792
♪ So be happy ♪

1251
01:39:06.876 --> 01:39:08.792
♪ For me ♪

1252
01:39:08.876 --> 01:39:11.334
♪ For you ♪

1253
01:39:11.417 --> 01:39:15.542
♪ Feel joy ♪♪

1254
01:39:16.542 --> 01:39:19.542
[mellow music playing]
